(hard specs \\\(contracts\\\)) Tj
50 383 Td
(these constraints prevent double-posts, drift, and distributed chaos.) Tj
50 355 Td
(1\\\) idempotency key \\\(required\\\)) Tj
50 339 Td
(  - every side-effect intent has a stable idempotencyKey) Tj
50 323 Td
(  - receipts must reference it) Tj
50 307 Td
(  - dedupe is based on receipts/state, not hope) Tj
50 280 Td
(2\\\) lease + ttl \\\(required\\\)) Tj
50 264 Td
(  - executor takes a lease before performing side effects) Tj
50 248 Td
(  - lease has ttl so another executor can safely take over after crash) Tj
50 221 Td
(3\\\) central rate limits \\\(required\\\)) Tj
50 205 Td
(  - rate limits are enforced per account/channel, centrally on the executor) Tj
50 189 Td
(  - adding more workers must not increase spam risk) Tj
50 162 Td
